## Vercel Speed Insights Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

### Changes Made:

1. **Installed Package:**
   - Added `@vercel/speed-insights` package using npm
   - Updated `package.json` and `package-lock.json` with the new dependency

2. **Modified Files:**
   - `frontend/src/app/layout.tsx`:
     - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
     - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the body element in the root layout

### Implementation Details:

- This is a Next.js 16.2.6 project using the App Router architecture
- Following the official documentation, the SpeedInsights component was added to the root layout file (`src/app/layout.tsx`)
- The component is placed just before the closing `</body>` tag, which is the recommended position per the docs
- The implementation uses the Next.js-specific package (`@vercel/speed-insights/next`) which is optimized for Next.js applications

### Verification:

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ No new linting errors introduced (existing linting errors in LiveActivityFeed.tsx are pre-existing and unrelated to this change)
✅ Lock files updated correctly with new dependency

### Next Steps:

After deployment to Vercel, Speed Insights will automatically start collecting performance data. You can:
1. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel dashboard (Project Settings → Speed Insights)
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Monitor real-time performance metrics in the Vercel dashboard

The `/_vercel/speed-insights/*` routes will be automatically available after deployment.
